      <p>Common repairs—thermostat replacement, heating element, pressure relief valve—run $200–$600 with parts and labor from a commercial plumber. Sediment buildup flushing and anode rod replacement are maintenance items that run $150–$400 and can extend heater life significantly. More significant repairs—heat exchanger failure, persistent mixing valve issues, gas valve replacement—run $400–$1,200+.</p>
