      <p>Philadelphia is one of the country's most distinctive food cities—with a restaurant scene shaped by its Italian market history, diverse immigrant communities, world-class chefs, and deeply loyal neighborhood dining culture. Philly restaurant owners face the same cash flow challenges as operators everywhere, with some specific to this market.</p>
